choices.text: Harmony used discarded paper to make notepads for her friends by folding five letter-sized pieces of paper three times, cutting along the lines, stacking the smaller note papers and stapling them together. If one person writes an average of ten notes per day on this notepad, it would last approximately 365 days (one year) before needing to be replaced.
